Combine 1 1/2 cups granola, apricots, cranberries and chocolate chips in a food processor; pulse until finely chopped, but not pasty. Transfer to a large mixing bowl. Add crispy rice cereal and remaining 1/2 cup granola; mix until well combined. Set aside. In medium saucepan over low heat, combine honey, peanut butter and vanilla; stir until well combined and bubbly (about 3 to 5 minutes). Remove from heat. Pour over cereal mixture and stir with a large wooden spoon. Press into a 13x9-inch pan. Refrigerate for several hours. Cut into bars.